== Soller Gambit ==
Black offers a second pawn with '''2...f6'''. Although it looks like a weakening move, White must be careful to avoid falling into potential traps.

White can capture the pawn with '''[[Chess Opening Theory/1. d4/1...e5/2. dxe5/2...f6/3. exf6|3. exf6]]''', but Black gains a lead in development in exchange after re-capturing with the knight.

Alternatively, White can give back the pawn by playing '''3. e4'''. Note that Black cannot immediately capture the e5 pawn as 3...fxe5?? loses to 4. Qh5+.

